issues.shortMessage: Add a nested comment explaining why this method is empty, throw a NotSupportedException or complete the implementation.
issues.fullMessage: There are several reasons for a method not to have a method body: It is an unintentional omission, and should be fixed. It is not yet, or never will be, supported. In this case an "NotSupportedException" should be thrown. The method is an intentionally-blank override. In this case a nested comment should explain the reason for the blank override.
